The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Tuesday, March 30, 2004 				 Threat slur on Amisha family
 CHANDRIMA S. BHATTACHARYA				 	 Amisha Patel: Under fire																								Mumbai, March 29: Actor Amisha Patels parents have allegedly threatened filmmaker Vikram Bhatt and his family and asked him to keep away from their daughter.																								Vikrams mother Varsha Bhatt has lodged a police complaint at the Versova police station against Amishas parents, Amit and Asha Patel, alleging that they made a threatening phone call to her. 																								Amisha and Vikram have shared a close relationship for some time and the actors parents are believed to be against it.																								Police said the complaint was lodged on Thursday under Section 506 (criminal intimidation).																								Asha denied that she and her husband had made the phone calls. I dont have any idea about what is happening. 																								She said Amisha was away for shooting. Vikram was not available for comment.																								Amisha is currently working on one of Vikrams projects called Ailan, for which they recently were in Switzerland. This is their second project together after Aap Mujhe Acchhe Lagne Lage.
